          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-06-24 21:28:51" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>organ in the mouth used for speaking and eating</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>tongue</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Though in {S:05900300500008} the tongue is referred to as a part of the body, it is used essentially as a symbol for speech, and since in some languages the tongue is not regarded as an organ of speech, but simply as a part of the mouth, it may be necessary to change the expression to read ‘the mouth is a small member of the body’ or ‘speaking is only a small part of one’s life.’ It is obviously not the tongue as an organ which corrupts the whole person, but the capacity for speech which has such a corrupting effect.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
